m) spacing. The timing and intensity of mortality shifted mixing effects on periodic annual increment slightly over time. Evidence for consistent overyielding among spacings was weak in these P. ponderosa/P. contorta and P. ponderosa/A. grandis spacing trials at total plantation age of 53 and 45 years, respectively. However, statistical power for detecting mixing effects was limited by the relatively small number of replications, and size differentiation continues to emerge at successively wider spacings on mixed-species plots.},
